## Source 2 — HITECH Act

The Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health Act strengthened HIPAA enforcement and extended certain requirements. HITECH is relevant to OpenMRS primarily for two provisions:

**Breach notification:** MyClinic must notify affected individuals and HHS within 60 days of discovering a breach of unsecured ePHI. Encryption of ePHI provides safe harbor from breach notification obligations — another reason the encryption requirements are effectively mandatory for MyClinic despite their addressable classification.

**Accounting of disclosures:** Patients have the right to request an accounting of disclosures of their ePHI. This requires that OpenMRS's audit logging capture not just internal access but external disclosures — when patient data was transmitted to the laboratory system, when billing records were sent to an insurer.

